response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Cubes\", \"description\": \"Given a list of integers, write a function that calculates the sum of their cubes.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_cubes(lst: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `lst` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of the cubes of the input integers.\", \"code\": \"def sum_of_cubes(lst: list[int]) -> int:\\n    return sum(i**3 for i in lst)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_cubes([1, 2, 3]) == 36\", \"assert sum_of_cubes([-1, -2, -3]) == -36\", \"assert sum_of_cubes([]) == 0\"] }"
